101. Symmetric Tree Description Given the root of a binary tree, check whether it is a mirror of itself (i.e., symmetric around its center).
&nbsp;
Example 1:
Input: root = [1,2,2,3,4,4,3] Output: true Example 2:
Input: root = [1,2,2,null,3,null,3] Output: false &nbsp;
Constraints:
The number of nodes in the tree is in the range [1, 1000]. -100 &lt;= Node.val &lt;= 100 &nbsp;
Follow up: Could you solve it both recursively and iteratively? Related Topics Tree Depth-First Search Breadth-First Search Binary Tree Similar Questions
